# Audio Effects — live-playback node-graph stubs
#
# These mirror a would-be runtime_audio_effects.c (pitch/filters/reverb/delay
# attached to an already-playing ma_sound* handle) and remain no-ops: doing
# this for real requires wiring miniaudio's ma_node_graph into the live
# playback engine (runtime_audio.c) and rebuilding+redeploying the runtime,
# which is out of scope here (see doc/03_plan/cert/redeploy_selfhost_plan.md
# for the in-flight toolchain redeploy this depends on). Returning 0 (not a
# fake success code) is the fail-closed contract callers rely on — e.g.
# audio_manager.spl's doppler code calls rt_audio_set_pitch and must be able
# to tell "not applied" from "applied".
#
# Real DSP effects DO now exist and are wired end-to-end, just on a
# different, decoupled path: offline PCM buffers (synthesized or decoded
# from WAV), not live ma_sound* handles. See
# src/lib/common/engine/audio/sound_synth.spl for the implementations
# (apply_lowpass/apply_highpass/apply_delay/reverb/apply_pitch_shift — all
# real one-pole filters / delay lines / Schroeder reverb / resample, not
# stubs) and src/app/sound/main.spl's `render`/`play` subcommands (sound.sdn
# `effects:` list, including `pitch`) for where they're applied. That is the
# "pure-Simple DSP path on decoded PCM" alternative to a live node-graph.
#
# These are the Simple-side implementations of the symbols declared as
# extern fn in audio_sffi.spl.

# Stub: set playback pitch on sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_set_pitch(sound_handle: i64, pitch: f64) -> i64:
    0

# Stub: attach a lowpass filter at cutoff_hz to sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_add_lowpass(sound_handle: i64, cutoff_hz: f64) -> i64:
    0

# Stub: attach a highpass filter at cutoff_hz to sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_add_highpass(sound_handle: i64, cutoff_hz: f64) -> i64:
    0

# Stub: attach a reverb effect to sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_add_reverb(sound_handle: i64, decay: f64, wet_dry: f64) -> i64:
    0

# Stub: attach a delay/echo effect to sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_add_delay(sound_handle: i64, time_ms: f64, feedback: f64) -> i64:
    0

# Stub: remove a previously attached effect_handle from sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_remove_effect(sound_handle: i64, effect_handle: i64) -> i64:
    0

# Stub: remove all effects from sound_handle (no-op until node-graph support lands).
fn rt_audio_clear_effects(sound_handle: i64) -> i64:
    0
